<TITLE> BDR killing charge-sheet by month-end </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 8 (bdnews24.com)Home minister Sahara Khatun has said the charges in the BDR killing case will be submitted by the month-end. "Trial will begin after the charges are pressed. The trial of mutiny outside Dhaka has already started in two districts." Ten sensational cases have been put on the list after sifting through cases countrywide, she told reporters after a meeting of the monitoring cell for sensational cases at the Secretariat. Moreover, the minister added, re-investigation has been ordered into six cases lodged during former BNP-Jamaat-e-Islami coalition government's tenure. The cases to be re-investigated are the bomb attack on a Kadiani mosque in Khulna in 2001, two cases regarding bombing of the Awami League office in Narayanganj in 2001, bomb attack on Sheikh Helal's meeting at Mollarhat in Bagerhat the same year, bomb attack on a house of Salla upazila health complex in 2001 and the bomb attack on the shrine of Shahjalal in Sylhet in 2004. "Alongside these cases, the case regarding the death of Gonotontri Party president Nurul Islam has also been included as a sensational case and investigation has been ordered," she added. Apart from the BDR killing case, 10-truck arms haul case in Chittagong, Chittagong BNP leader and businessman Jamal Uddin killing case, Dr Tamanna murder case and the case regarding the killing of Taher Sujon of Nandail have been included in the list of sensational cases to immediately start the trial, Sahara said. Regarding the activities of Indian insurgents United Liberation Front of Assam in Bangladesh, she said, "We don't know who is doing what, when and where. But the intelligence agencies are keen to catch them and a good number of terrorists have been arrested already." State minister for home Shamsul Huq Tuku, home secretary Abdus Sobhan Sikder and RAB chief Hassan Mahmud Khandaker were present. bdnews2
